Ran across this random shot of a Canada Goose from Calif. in the archives & was struck by how different the head looks from the locals here on the East Coast. I think it's mostly the lower crown & flatter culmen -- the B. c. canadensis here in NJ usually have a much more dish-shaped face. I believe this is ssp. moffitti. www.idahobirds.net/identification/identification.html has links to 3 authoritative descriptions of Canada & Cackling geese & theirr subspecies.
